Job Description:


Provide full spectrum of human resources supports including but not limited to recruitment, on-boarding arrangement, leave and payroll administration, staff benefit projects, employee relations activities etc.;
Ensure accurate and updated staff records are maintained;
Prepare periodical management reports and organization charts;
Assist in ad-hoc projects as required.
Requirement:

Degree holder in Human Resources Management or related discipline;
At least 2 years’ relevant experience preferable in sizable companies;
Good interpersonal skill and able to deal with different levels of people;
Strong command of both spoken and written English, Chinese and Mandarin;
Independent, committed, responsible, self-motivated, detailed-minded and proactive;
Immediate available is preferred.

ROLES & RESPONSIBILITIES:

Responsible for recruitment process including interview and selection, handle employees on-boarding to off-boarding, verification of candidate's qualification and visa application procedures;
Responsible for issuing employment contract and other personnel letters;
Perform payroll functions including monthly payroll, MPF, and filing of tax return;
Liaise with the Government departments to ensure compliance with Employment Ordinance, Inland Revenue Ordinances, etc;
Liaise with different services providers such as broker, insurers and MPF trustee for HR operations;
Support the development and implementation HR policies, procedures and HR system;
To maintain accurate employee record in HR system and filing system;
Responsible for daily HR operations and general staff enquiries; and
Handle ad-hoc projects as assigned.

REQUIREMENTS:

Higher diploma or above in Human Resources Management or related disciplines;
Be well-versed in Employment Ordinance and human resource business functions;
At least 1 year of human resources experience;
Have self-motivation, strong analytical and coordination skills;
Able to handle sensitive information with confidentiality;
Able to work under pressure and finish tasks with tight deadline; and
Possess excellent command written and spoken English and Chinese languages (including Putonghua).

Appointment will initially be made on contract basis for up to two years, renewable subject to performance.

Responsibilities:

To provide HR account services to designated Business Units/Corporate Units, including recruitment, staff retention, staff relations, disciplinary and performance management.
To maintain HR related records, such as headcount summary and HRIS staff record etc.;
To prepare monthly management reports and analysis;
To perform ad hoc projects or duties as assigned by supervisor

Requirements:

Degree holder in Human Resources Management or related disciplines;
Minimum 6 years working experience in human resources;
Proficiency in MS Excel, Word PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Good communication and interpersonal skills;
Willing to learn and a good team player.
Immediate available is an advantage

We offer an attractive remuneration & benefit package and 5-day work.  Please click the Apply Now button to send your full resume stating relevant job reference, present and expected salary and availability.

Personal data collected will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment related purposes only.

The ideal candidate will need to have experiences in account services as a temporary HR Executive.  

Main Responsibilities:

Assist in projects related to human resources development, e.g. full spectrum of HR functions, including but not limited to HRIS System, selection & planning, performance management, remuneration management, etc.;
Responsible for the full spectrum of Talent Acquisition, from shortlisting resumes, interviewing, making an offer before the candidates’ onboarding and related recruitment aspects;
Review and implement organizational charts, HR policies, procedures, and practices from time to time;
Work closely with relevant parties internally and externally to meet the business needs;
Provide support to employees in various HR-related topics such as leaves, ER or any issues that may arise;
Other ad-hoc projects when necessary.

Job Requirements:

Degree in Human Resources or related fields;
2 - 5 years of experience in a HR Generalist role;
Proficient in both written and spoken Chinese, Mandarin and English;
Knowledge in Recruitment, Employee Relations, Performance Management, Compensation and HK Labour Ordinance;
Experience in using any HRIS systems will be an advantage;
Good at interpersonal and communication skills;
Immediate available is preferred.

Remuneration will commensurate with candidate’s qualification and experience. Interested candidates please send your detailed resume with present & expected salary to Human Resources Department, 18/F, Tower B, 223 – 231 Wai Yip Street, Kwun Tong, Kowloon, Hong Kong

Please complete the standard application procedure by clicking the Apply Now button.

The information provided will be kept confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants not contacted within three months may consider their applications unsuccessful. The company will retain all applications for a maximum period of one year.

The Role
To cope with our aggressive growth and expansion plan, we are inviting high caliber individuals to join our fast growth team.  You will have a chance to work at a fast-paced mission driven company that brings material science to life and benefit the mass.  We are bringing business disruption and new hygiene standard to the world with the introduction of new photocatalyst products and services. With the continuous R&D and business innovation, we are thrilled to develop the next generation technology that safeguards everyday life.  

Responsibilities

Communicate and manage the recruitment requests of BUs/Hiring Managers;
Develop and manage recruitment process effectively from posting job advertisements, screening resumes, conducting interviews, confirming offer and recruitment project management;
Provide end-to-end recruitment process to ensure hiring needs are fulfilled timely and effectively, support hiring managers to further develop and strengthen the talent pool;
Develop effective hiring channels and methodologies for recruitment pipeline;
Prepare hiring tracking reports and liaise with hiring manager on the progress;
Prepare HR reports and data analysis on staff turnover, retention, career development, etc;
Assist in any other HR duties as assigned.
Requirements

Degree in Human Resources Management, Business Management or related disciplines;
Minimum 3 years of solid recruiting experience in fast-paced business environment with proven expertise from FMCG or consumer healthcare market is a MUST;
Mature, self-motivated, ability to prioritize multiple tasks and work under pressure;
Strong PC skills, well-versed in Microsoft applications and Chinese word processing
Immediate available is highly preferred;
Fluent in written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin.
We offer the right candidate attractive remuneration package and outstanding prospects for career advancement and development.  The right candidate will progress career in a forward thinking and dynamic business with exciting growth plans.  If you are qualified and interested, please send your full resume with current & expected salary and availability by clicking "APPLY".

All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

THE JOB

Reporting to the Human Resources Officer (Appointment), the Human Resources Assistant (Appointment) will be responsible for the following duties:
Provide administration support in recruitment and appointment related matters such as advertisement preparation, interview arrangement, work visa application/extension, contract renewal, annual appraisal exercise, training and development programme;
Maintain and update personnel records in HRIS;
Assist in annual staff cost budget;
Prepare financial statistics and reports;
Assist in ad-hoc/regular project; and
Perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.
THE REQUIREMENTS
Applicants should have: (1) a minimum of 5 passes in HKCEE or 5 HKDSE subjects with at least Level 2 or equivalent, including English, Chinese and Mathematics; or (2) any post secondary qualification;
Possess certificate/ diploma in human resources management or related discipline;
Strong knowledge and application in Employment Ordinance, MPF regulations and other related legislations;
Strong in numeracy and good communication skills;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese.  Ability to speak Putonghua is an advantage; and
Proficient in HRIS system and MS-Excel.

[Applicants who have responded to the previous advertisements need not re-apply. Their applications are being considered accordingly.]




APPLICATIONS

Please send the completed Application Form with indication of expected salary to The Human Resources Manager, Hong Kong Sports Institute Ltd, 25 Yuen Wo Road, Sha Tin, New Territories or email: hrdept@ hksi.org.hk on or before 23 January 2022. Please quote reference no. JD-20220110-HRA(APPOINTMENT) in the application.
Appointment will be on a fixed term contract. General information is available at the website http://www.hksi.org.hk. 
Applicants who are not invited for interview within six months may consider their applications unsuccessful.
All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence. Personal Data provided by appointees will be used strictly for recruitment and other employment-related purposes only.



THE HKSI IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Responsibilities:

Generate content for marketing & recruitment purposes;
Manage recruitment platforms and arrange recruitment interviews;
Follow up with new recruit;
Plan training schedule and manage the new members;
Manage and assist in all projects and tasks as assigned;
Provide human resources support to the sales team.

 Requirements:


Diploma or above;
Minimum 3 years of experience preferably in training or front-line business functions with Insurance or banking sector;
Fluent Cantonese and English;
Familiar with MS Office application (Word, Excel & Power Point);
Familiar with Photoshop is an advantage;
Responsible, detail-minded & self-motivated;
Able to work independently.

 We Offer:

Convenient working location: Tsim Sha Tsui;
5 days working (9:30 A.M. - 6:00 P.M.);
Salary with high performance bonus;
Medical Insurance;
Public Holiday.

We offer 5-day work and an attractive package to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your resume with current and expected salary to us.
(All applications received will be treated in strict confidence and solely for recruitment purpose.)

Responsibilities:



Work with various hiring managers to identify recruitment needs and to develop effective recruitment strategy;
Able to source qualified candidates through a wide variety of channels;
Handle full set of recruitment cycle from screening & interviewing to closure of offers;
Educate candidates on the career growth potential and compensation philosophy;
Conduct professional conversations with hiring managers and candidates about feedback during the recruitment process in a timely manner;
Share meaningful market data, employment trends and industry knowledge with hiring managers;
Utilize the functionality of the candidate tracking system and maintain data integrity and controls; and
Work as part of the HR and Admin Team to achieve company goal and objectives.

Requirements:


Diploma / Degree holder with any disciplines;
Minimum 2 years of solid IT recruitment experience in a fast-paced, in-house environment is essential.
Ability to develop creative and diverse sourcing strategies, including use of technology and market mapping;
Experience of end-to-end recruitment from interviewing to managing offer process up to middle levels of positions;
Must be result driven, highly-motivated and able to work under pressure with a can-do attitude;
Outstanding interpersonal skill and ability to build strong relationship with candidates;
Prior experience in handling sensitive/confidential information; and
Fluent in English and Chinese, both written and spoken.
Less experience will be considered as Talent Acquisition Assistant.

If interested, please send your detailed resume with availability, current and expected salary to us.  All information provided will be treated in strict confidential and used solely for recruitment purposes.

All resumes will be retained for a period of two years for recruitment purpose only in accordance with the Company’s Privacy Policy.

Location: Sheung Wan

Roles & responsibilities:

Lead an appointment unit to manage the corporate human resources matters pertaining to community services in Tung Wah including manpower planning, pay review, recruitment and appointment as well as staff discipline and complaints;
develop and implement human resources policies to meet the corporate objectives and service needs;
undertake regular review of personnel administration system and procedures as well as assigned ad hoc projects/tasks to cope with changing needs;
provide executive support to the secretarial office of the Human Resources Committee; and
undertake ad hoc projects and other general administrative duties including management of departmental business, supervision of staff and organization of meetings.

The ideal candidate should possess:

A recognized degree or equivalent, preferably human resources management;
at least Grade D in English Language (Syllabus B) and Chinese Language in the HKCEE or equivalent;
at least 4 years’ post-qualification administration experience, preferably human resources management/public administration;
proficiency in English and Chinese; and
good communication and interpersonal skills.

(Please specify in the application form the HKCEE result and relevant working experience you have attained in detail.)

Compensation & employment terms:

The successful candidate will initially be offered a 3-year contract with a remuneration package which will be commensurate with his/her background and experience.  The continuation of employment and employment terms thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement.  Apart from contributions to the MPF Scheme, other benefits include paid annual leave, medical services, a dental scheme and training sponsorships.  The incumbent will normally work under a 5-day week schedule subject to operational needs and exigencies of the service.

Application:

Please send your resume and a completed application form [F601(n)] with indication of your current and expected salaries to the Head of Human Resources Division, Tung Wah Group of Hospitals at 4/F., Wong Fung Ling Memorial Building, 12 Po Yan Street, Hong Kong by 20 January 2022.  Application forms are obtainable in person or can be downloaded from http://www.tungwah.org.hk.  The reference code should be marked both in the letter and on the envelope.  Underpaid mail items will not be accepted by Tung Wah.  For proper delivery of your mail items, please ensure your mail items bear sufficient postage with return address before posting.  Personal data provided by applicants will be used strictly for recruitment purpose only and in accordance with the Tung Wah’s personal data policy.  Applicants not invited to attend an interview by 30 April 2022 may assume that their applications are unsuccessful.

WE ARE AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Responsibilities:

Provide full spectrum of human resources support including but not limited to recruitment, payroll administration, compensation and benefits, performance management, training and staff relations;
Able to manage monthly payroll, final payment and related calculation via system independently;
Assist in reviewing and formulating HR policies and procedures;
Ensure compliance with employment and related legislations;
Prepare and maintain documentation and reports from staff onboarding to offboarding; and
Opportunities to participate in ad hoc projects as assigned.

Requirements:

Diploma or Degree holder in Human Resources or related disciplines;
Minimum 4-5 years’ relevant experience with exposure in NGO will be an advantage but not a must;
Well-versed in Hong Kong Employment Ordinance;
Detail-minded, self-motivated and demonstrates ability to work independently and contributes as a strong team player;
Excellent problem-solving, communication and organizational skills;
Excellent command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Proficiency in MS Word, Excel and Chinese word processing;
Immediate available is preferred;
Candidate with more experience may be considered for a more senior role

Staff Benefits:

Regular Sunday and Public Holidays off
14 to 18 days’ annual leave entitlement
Medical benefits to staff and dependent
On-the-job training and training sponsorship & study leave

Interested parties please send full resume with last and expected salary to Human Resources Unit, United Christian Nethersole Community Health Service, L1, KEC Administrative Building, No. 2 Po Ning Lane, Hang Hau, Tseung Kwan O with job reference no. marked on the envelope or by clicking "Apply Now"

(Applicants not invited for interview within 4 weeks from the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful. All personal data collected will be treated in strict confidence and will only be used for recruitment related purpose.)

The Role
To cope with our aggressive growth and expansion plan, we are inviting high caliber individuals to join our fast growth team.  You will have a chance to work at a fast-paced mission driven company that brings material science to life and benefit the mass.  We are bringing business disruption and new hygiene standard to the world with the introduction of new photocatalyst products and services. With the continuous R&D and business innovation, we are thrilled to develop the next generation technology that safeguards everyday life.  The ideal candidate will support the full scope of Human Resources responsibilities and partner with the organization on strategic initiatives. Maintain and enhance the organization's human resources by planning, implementing, and evaluating human resources policies, programs, and practices.

Responsibilities

Design and implement human resources strategies including talent acquisition, staffing retention, employment compensation, health and welfare benefits, training and development, and labour relations, etc;
Work closely with top management by providing human resources advice, counsel, and decisions; accountable for the performance of HR function;
Suggest appropriate innovative measures for improving performance evaluations and employee engagement;
Translate the business strategy into HR strategy and provide human capital and organizational change perspectives embedded into business leadership teams;
Align and integrate HR strategies, goals and practices to ensure high performing culture/employees/teams; 
Drive leadership development and address organizational issues. Professional support in all change processes. 
Requirements

Degree holder or above in Human Resources Management or related disciplines;
At least 10 years of solid HR experience with minimum 5 years' experience in supervisory level and HRBP role; 
Solid HR practical experience within fast-paced business environment in FMCG or consumer healthcare industry is a MUST;
Strong capability to work with different levels of stakeholders;
Good negotiation, motivation, strategic and leadership skills to drive success and create win-win solutions;
Possess good planning, organizational and time management skills;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills; able to interact with different levels of people;
Strong working knowledge of employment law issues, best practice processes for disciplinary, redundancies and payroll is required, as well as experience of employee relations;
Fluent in written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin.
We offer the right candidate attractive remuneration package and outstanding prospects for career advancement and development.  The right candidate will progress career in a forward thinking and dynamic business with exciting growth plans.  If you are qualified and interested, please send your full resume with current & expected salary and availability by clicking "APPLY".

All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

Job Functions


Assist in formulating the definition, revision and release of software development related processes, procedures and templates;
Responsible for the promotion of processes, procedures and templates;
Develop a software quality assurance plan for the project;
Audit the process and products of the project according to the software quality assurance plan. Issue an audit report to assist the project team in resolving audit findings;
Follow up the problems found in the project audit process until the problems are solved;
Collect improvement suggestions on processes and templates from each project team, formulate and continuously improve the software development process according to the company and project conditions;
Verify the relevant measurement data provided by the project, identify potential project issues via data analysis.
Provide process management and quality assurance consulting or training for related projects;
Timely report the findings in audit of process and work product audit in the project to superiors, project managers, and ODC managers with objective insight

Job Requirements

More than 3 years of software industry experience, and more than 2 years of software quality assurance experience;
Possess basic knowledge of software development, software engineering, and quality management system;
Possess the basic ability of technical review and process audit;
Have statistics-related knowledge, and be able to use statistical methods well for quality analysis, control and management capabilities
Cheerful personality, teamwork spirit and good communication and coordination skills;
Have good language organization ability and document writing ability;
Have experience in training internal employees;
Good level of English and Mandarin;
Familiar with CMMI or ISO9001 is preferred.

Our client, the world’s leading provider of genomic sequencing services and proteomic services, dedicated to hire an all rounded Human Resources Officer to support their daily operations.

Responsibilities:

Perform all rounded HR Generalist duties major in Compensation & Benefits and daily operations
Handle MPF administration, taxation, payroll calculation and prepare final payment
Administrate monthly payroll for the companies
Assist in coordinate employee relations activities, training arrangement, delivery of in-house training & seminar
Compile regular HR related statistics and reports for management review
Participate in ad hoc duties as assigned

Requirements

Degree in Human Resources Management or related disciplines;
At least  years solid experience in Human Resources, preferably in healthcare, medical industry;
Well versed in Hong Kong Employment Ordinance and other HR related ordinances;
Positive thinking, attentive to details, independent and good team-player;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Proficient in MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing;
Good commend in both written and spoken English & Chinese

***Immediate available is highly preferred

To apply for this position, please simply click on the “APPLY NOW” bottom to forward an up-to-date copy of your resume. All applications will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purposes only. If this job isn't quite right for you but you are looking for a new position, please contact Ms. Fung at 6110-5379 for a confidential discussion on your career.

Perrett Laver is now seeking to hire a bright, dynamic and ambitious individual to join our fast-growing team in Central Hong Kong as Research Associate.



This role draws upon the intellectual skills necessary to grasp a complex brief; the research skills to identify people who are at the highest levels in their professions; the advocacy skills to engage such candidates; the motivation to serve our clients to the best of our abilities; and the capacity to work as part of a core project team and a wider corporate team. You will have a thirst for knowledge, a methodical mind-set that will enable you to carry out a comprehensive and global search of the talent pool, and high attention to detail.



Research Associates are expected to manage the research phase of the project including background analysis, identification and securing of candidates, and candidate care. They work closely with and support the Project Management Team and the Consultant(s) in the delivery of projects through to the appointment of a preferred candidate.



We are seeking people with the following:

Outstanding verbal and written communication skills in both English and Chinese;
A Master’s degree or above;
A strong sense of service and the drive to best support our clients and candidates;
Knowledge and passion in education and non-profit sector;
An intellectually curious mind-set;
A shared commitment to the mission and values of Perrett Laver;
Sharp and rigorous analytical skills and attention to detail, particularly regarding the assessment of candidates;
Ability to manage multiple projects and to prioritize workload;
A willingness to work with flexible hours when needed;
Strong appreciation and understanding of the importance of punctuality, responsibility and discretion required for this role;
Tenacious, committed and results-oriented;
Enthusiastic and proactive;
Collaborative, flexible and able to contribute to the development of a growing team;
Fresh graduates are welcome to apply

Desirable

A Graduate degree;
Fluent in Cantonese and Mandarin;
Experience working within universities, academic organizations or schools or NGO.

No previous experience working in executive search is required. Perrett Laver will provide rigorous and systematic training for all new hires.

To Apply

To apply, please submit an up-to-date CV and Cover Letter via https://candidates.perrettlaver.com/vacancies/ , quoting reference HKPL/RES.
